---
title: Soy-Glazed Steak with Asparagus Stir-Fry plus Jasmine Rice & Scallion-Ginger Oil
description: This stir-fry is a flavor supernova! The star? Steak that you’ll sear, slice, and drizzle with a glossy soy glaze amped up with sweet chili sauce and nutty sesame dressing. Sprinkle that steak with crackly sesame seeds and serve it alongside a stir-fry of asparagus, scallion, and onion. Fluffy jasmine rice elevated with aromatic scallion-ginger oil rounds out this explosion of deliciousness.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6863c4115e6b2bfce953a816-4adfed0d.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6864ed6d6c81f96af0603b4c-en-US.pdf
cuisine: East Asia
nutrition:
  calories: 940 kcal
  fat: 41 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 102 g
  sugar: 32 g
  protein: 36 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 1590 mg
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/soy-glazed-steak-with-asparagus-stir-fry-6864ed6d6c81f96af0603b4c
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
---

Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince @ginger{1%thumb}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}. Trim and discard woody bottom ends from @asparagus{12%ounce}; cut stalks crosswise into 1-inch pieces.

In a small #pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1/4 cups water, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, pat @ranch steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large #stainless steel pan{} over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

== Scallion-Ginger Oil ==

In a small microwave-safe #bowl{}, combine ginger, scallion greens, 2 TBSP oil, and a pinch of salt. Cover bowl with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Stir and set aside.

== Asparagus Stir-Fry ==

Heat a large drizzle of oil in pan used for steak over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites, onion, and asparagus. Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and lightly browned, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Stir in @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}, @sesame dressing{1.5%ounce}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}, and 1/4 cup water; cook, stirring, until sauce has thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

== To Serve ==

Thinly slice steak against the grain.

Divide rice and asparagus stir-fry between plates in separate sections; top stir-fry with steak. Drizzle any remaining sauce from pan over steak. Spoon as much scallion-ginger oil over rice as you like.

Garnish with @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon} and serve.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.